HEADWORD: Stallage
<hw>Stall"age</hw> <pr>(st⟦add⟧l"⟦asl⟧j ; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>estallage</ets>, of German origin. See
<er>Stall</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>The right of erecting a stall or stalls in fairs; rent paid for a
stall.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dung of cattle or horses, mixed with straw.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stallation</ent>⟦br⟧
